"""
Monitoring API Router

API endpoints for accessing pattern monitoring data, metrics, alerts,
and audit trail information.
"""

from datetime import datetime, timedelta
from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional

from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, Query
from pydantic import BaseModel, Field

from app.service.agent.patterns.base import PatternType
from app.service.monitoring.pattern_alerts import (
    AlertCondition,
    AlertNotification,
    AlertSeverity,
    AlertStatus,
    get_alert_manager,
)
from app.service.monitoring.pattern_audit import AuditEventType, get_audit_trail
from app.service.monitoring.pattern_metrics import get_metrics_collector

router = APIRouter(prefix="/api/v1/monitoring", tags=["monitoring"])


# Response Models
class MetricsSummaryResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for metrics summary"""

    pattern_type: str
    total_executions: int
    success_rate: float
    avg_duration: float
    total_cost: float
    avg_confidence: float
    token_usage: Dict[str, int]


class AlertResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for alerts"""

    id: str
    condition_name: str
    pattern_type: str
    severity: str
    status: str
    title: str
    description: str
    current_value: float
    threshold: float
    created_at: datetime
    resolved_at: Optional[datetime] = None
    acknowledged_at: Optional[datetime] = None


class AlertSummaryResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for alert summary"""

    active_alerts: int
    critical_alerts: int
    warning_alerts: int
    conditions_count: int
    notifications_count: int


class AuditEventResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for audit events"""

    id: str
    event_type: str
    pattern_type: Optional[str] = None
    user_id: Optional[str] = None
    session_id: Optional[str] = None
    investigation_id: Optional[str] = None
    title: str
    description: Optional[str] = None
    context: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
    metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
    decision_factors: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None
    alternatives_considered: Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]] = None
    success: Optional[bool] = None
    confidence_score: Optional[int] = None
    created_at: datetime
    ip_address: Optional[str] = None
    user_agent: Optional[str] = None


class PatternUsageStatsResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for pattern usage statistics"""

    pattern_type: str
    selection_count: int
    execution_count: int
    success_count: int
    failure_count: int
    success_rate: float


class UserActivityResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for user activity"""

    user_id: str
    total_events: int
    pattern_selections: int
    user_actions: int
    recent_events: List[Dict[str, Any]]


# Request Models
class AlertConditionRequest(BaseModel):
    """Request model for creating alert conditions"""

    name: str
    description: str
    metric_name: str
    threshold: float
    operator: str
    duration_minutes: int = 5
    severity: AlertSeverity = AlertSeverity.WARNING
    pattern_types: Optional[List[PatternType]] = None
    enabled: bool = True


class AlertNotificationRequest(BaseModel):
    """Request model for creating alert notifications"""

    name: str
    type: str  # email, slack, webhook, pagerduty
    config: Dict[str, Any]
    severities: List[AlertSeverity] = [AlertSeverity.CRITICAL, AlertSeverity.WARNING]
    pattern_types: Optional[List[PatternType]] = None
    enabled: bool = True


# Metrics Endpoints
@router.get("/metrics/summary")
async def get_metrics_summary(
    pattern_type: Optional[PatternType] = Query(
        None, description="Filter by pattern type"
    )
) -> List[MetricsSummaryResponse]:
    """Get metrics summary for patterns"""

    metrics_collector = get_metrics_collector()

    if pattern_type:
        pattern_types = [pattern_type]
    else:
        pattern_types = list(PatternType)

    summaries = []
    for pt in pattern_types:
        summary = metrics_collector.get_pattern_summary(pt)
        summaries.append(MetricsSummaryResponse(**summary))

    return summaries


@router.get("/metrics/pattern/{pattern_type}")
async def get_pattern_metrics(
    pattern_type: PatternType,
    hours: int = Query(24, ge=1, le=168, description="Hours of data to retrieve"),
) -> MetricsSummaryResponse:
    """Get detailed metrics for a specific pattern"""

    metrics_collector = get_metrics_collector()
    summary = metrics_collector.get_pattern_summary(pattern_type)

    return MetricsSummaryResponse(**summary)


@router.get("/metrics/usage")
async def get_usage_metrics(
    pattern_type: Optional[PatternType] = Query(
        None, description="Filter by pattern type"
    ),
    hours: int = Query(24, ge=1, le=168, description="Hours of data to retrieve"),
) -> Dict[str, Any]:
    """Get pattern usage metrics"""

    # This would typically query the metrics backend
    # For now, return mock data
    return {
        "total_executions": 1250,
        "unique_users": 45,
        "avg_executions_per_user": 27.8,
        "most_used_pattern": "prompt_chaining",
        "least_used_pattern": "evaluator_optimizer",
        "pattern_distribution": {
            "prompt_chaining": 35,
            "augmented_llm": 25,
            "routing": 20,
            "parallelization": 10,
            "orchestrator_workers": 8,
            "evaluator_optimizer": 2,
        },
    }


# Alert Endpoints
@router.get("/alerts")
async def get_alerts(
    status: Optional[AlertStatus] = Query(None, description="Filter by alert status"),
    severity: Optional[AlertSeverity] = Query(
        None, description="Filter by alert severity"
    ),
    pattern_type: Optional[PatternType] = Query(
        None, description="Filter by pattern type"
    ),
) -> List[AlertResponse]:
    """Get alerts with optional filtering"""

    alert_manager = get_alert_manager()

    if status == AlertStatus.ACTIVE:
        alerts = alert_manager.get_active_alerts()
    else:
        # Get all alerts from history
        alerts = alert_manager.get_alert_history(hours=24)

    # Apply filters
    if severity:
        alerts = [a for a in alerts if a.severity == severity]

    if pattern_type:
        alerts = [a for a in alerts if a.pattern_type == pattern_type]

    return [AlertResponse(**alert.dict()) for alert in alerts]

    alert_manager = get_alert_manager()

    user_id: str = Query(..., description="User ID acknowledging the alert"),
) -> Dict[str, str]:
    """Acknowledge an alert"""

    alert_manager = get_alert_manager()
    await alert_manager.acknowledge_alert(alert_id, user_id)

    return {"message": f"Alert {alert_id} acknowledged by {user_id}"}

async def create_alert_condition(condition: AlertConditionRequest) -> Dict[str, str]:
    """Create a new alert condition"""

    alert_manager = get_alert_manager()

    alert_condition = AlertCondition(**condition.dict())
    alert_manager.add_condition(alert_condition)

    return {"message": f"Alert condition '{condition.name}' created successfully"}


@router.delete("/alerts/conditions/{condition_name}")
async def delete_alert_condition(condition_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:

    alert_manager = get_alert_manager()

    return {"message": f"Alert condition '{condition_name}' deleted successfully"}

    alert_notification = AlertNotification(**notification.dict())

        "message": f"Notification channel '{notification.name}' created successfully"

    return {
        "message": f"Notification channel '{notification_name}' deleted successfully"

        None, description="Filter by pattern type"
    ),
    event_type: Optional[AuditEventType] = Query(
